Greek anti-terrorism police have detained more than 20 people in raids in Athens and seized heavy weaponry including anti-tank arms, authorities say. Press reports said the detainees were Kurds living in Greece. The statement said that in one of the locations raided police discovered a secret tunnel but provided no further information. READ ALSO  Banker in court for stealing deceased customers’ N3.6m A police statement said the raids in two central Athens locations followed co-operation with Greece’s secret service. 